race.comment: HAYEK (8) started ($1.50 fav) on resumption when a commanding on pace winner over 900m at Newcastle in fast time. Goes up a few levels for this and will prove hard to catch again. NORTON ROAD (1) has come back a much stronger commodity this prep with a career peak first-up. Nailed on the line with the 61kg when second over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Gets map favours again with a fitness edge over the bulk of these. SUNDAY TYCOON (6) races best with his runs spaced and Jason Collett goes on today. Won at the trip and can stalk the fast tempo. Each-way. DETENDU (2) resumes after bumping into some handy types at his last two campaigns. Looked tuned right up for this with a slick trial winner over 818m at Warwick Farm. Berry sticks and can sprint well fresh.
